<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,282,561]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,354,380]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">Distribution</emphasis>
. Atlantic and Indian Oceans, Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Vinogradov, M. E. &amp; Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N." box="[900,1163,354,381]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" refId="ref16750" refString="Vinogradov, M. E., Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N. (1996) Hyperiid amphipods (Amphipoda, Hyperiidea) of the world oceans. Oxonian Press Pvt. Ltd., New Delhi, 632 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Vinogradov 
<emphasis box="[1041,1090,354,380]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">et al</emphasis>
. 1996
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia Madrigal, M. S." box="[1173,1425,354,380]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" pagination="63 - 195" refId="ref14782" refString="Garcia Madrigal, M. S. (2007) Annotated checklist of the amphipods (Peracarida: Amphipoda) from the tropical eastern Pacific. Contributions to the Study of East Pacific Crustaceans, 4 (2), 63 - 195." type="journal article" year="2007">García Madrigal 2007</bibRefCitation>
). In the eastern Pacific from 
<collectingRegion box="[465,581,390,416]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">California</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[594,653,390,416]" name="United States of America" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">USA</collectingCountry>
, to 
<collectingRegion box="[697,871,390,416]" country="Mexico" name="Baja California" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">Baja California</collectingRegion>
and the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[1065,1181,390,416]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">California</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1194,1282,390,416]" name="Mexico" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, and south to 
<geoCoordinate box="[151,231,426,452]" degrees="38" direction="south" minutes="6" orientation="latitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" precision="925" value="-38.1">38°6’S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[243,346,426,452]" degrees="88" direction="west" minutes="02" orientation="longitude" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" precision="925" value="-88.03333">88°02’W</geoCoordinate>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia Madrigal, M. S." box="[360,614,426,452]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" pagination="63 - 195" refId="ref14782" refString="Garcia Madrigal, M. S. (2007) Annotated checklist of the amphipods (Peracarida: Amphipoda) from the tropical eastern Pacific. Contributions to the Study of East Pacific Crustaceans, 4 (2), 63 - 195." type="journal article" year="2007">García Madrigal 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="171" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,282,561]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,462,488]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Siegel-Causey, D." box="[322,566,462,488]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" refId="ref16354" refString="Siegel-Causey, D. (1982) Factors determining the distribution of hyperiid Amphipoda in the Gulf of California. Ph. D. Thesis, University of Arizona, Tucson, Arizona, 535 pp." type="book" year="1982">Siegel-Causey (1982)</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName box="[674,776,462,488]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lestrigonidae" genus="Hyperiietta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luzoni">
<emphasis box="[674,776,462,488]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">H. luzoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a very rare species in the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[1189,1306,462,488]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="2" pageNumber="171">California</collectingRegion>
. During his study it was recorded from two sites only, in the epipelagic layers in the southern Gulf and in deep water (
<quantity box="[1341,1428,498,525]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.087" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" unit="m" value="1087.0">1087 m</quantity>
) in the northern Gulf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia Madrigal, M. S." box="[388,654,534,560]" pageId="2" pageNumber="171" pagination="63 - 195" refId="ref14782" refString="Garcia Madrigal, M. S. (2007) Annotated checklist of the amphipods (Peracarida: Amphipoda) from the tropical eastern Pacific. Contributions to the Study of East Pacific Crustaceans, 4 (2), 63 - 195." type="journal article" year="2007">García Madrigal (2007)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned it as an epipelagic, coastal species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
